10. Calls for increased bilateral contacts to achieve a peaceful settlement.
Here is a concise summary of the Security Council document:

The Security Council:

* Urges the Georgian and Abkhaz sides to implement confidence-building measures without conditions to facilitate the safe return of refugees and internally displaced persons (para 11);
* Supports the principles for the distribution of competencies between Tbilisi and Sukhumi and welcomes additional ideas for a political dialogue (para 12);
* Encourages contacts between civil society representatives and appeals to both sides to promote active engagement (para 13);
* Underlines the primary responsibility of both sides to provide security and ensure freedom of movement for UNOMIG, CIS peacekeeping force, and other international personnel (para 14);
* Welcomes efforts to implement the Secretary-General's zero-tolerance policy on sexual exploitation and abuse (para 15);
* Extends the mandate of UNOMIG until 15 October 2008 (para 16);
* Requests the Secretary-General to encourage and support the parties in implementing confidence-building measures and establishing a meaningful dialogue (para 17);
* Supports the efforts of the Special Representative of the Secretary-General and the Group of Friends of the Secretary-General (para 18);
* Decides to remain actively seized of the matter (para 19).
